Moxa therapy or moxibustion is a common health therapy practiced in China, Japan, Korea, Vietnam, Tibet and Mongolia. It is a “warming” technique using the herb mugwort or Ai Ya. Moxibustion helps to increase blood circulation, tonify energy, stimulate the digestive system and boost the immune.
While its benefits still require a lot more research, moxa has been shown to help fight serious diseases and maladies, from cancer to joint pain.
@followers @highlight

An ode to the ineffable power of nature beyond our understanding. This is a medley of Mongolian folk songs about on a sunrise and a mirage on the horizons of the grassland, where light meets land in a moment of mystery. Grateful to have Peadar’s overtone throat singing and hulusi (Chinese gourd pipe) playing, Tyler on the kit and Aki on the keys as part of this journey with Sounds.

Full video on https://youtu.be/xU9SLHGDtIQ
